details.description:
Sustainability is the driver and focus of our coffee concept. Quality, ethical sourcing, and flavor are the criteria we search for when identifying local roasters to source our coffee beans. Featuring carefully curated coffee, tea, and juices, our expansive menu is reflective of the never-ending search for rich flavors and uncompromising quality. Our goal is to foster a community network of local business where people can develop an appreciation for local products. Choosing local roasters supports our community and guarantees the quality and freshness of our menu items.

There’s something special about the ritual of grabbing a fresh cup of coffee to get your day started or catching up with friends in our beloved Community.

reviews_data.review_text: Cozy spot with a friendly vibe! I’ve tried different matchas and every single one was amazing. They make the drinks quick, the inside is super cute, and they have a great playlist too :)

this is my go to spot almost 4 times a week and Im happy they got a good crowd now but today i waited here for almost 1 hour just to get a coffee ordering alone took 30 minutes not coz of huge line but slow service. will update the rating after another try
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Sam. We thank you for your support and sincerely appreciate your business. reviews_data.review_text: Hilltop coffee I love it

I 100% recommend Hilltop Coffee! I got the matcha latte with vanilla and sweet cream, and it was honestly one of the best matchas I’ve ever had, definitely a 10/10. I also tried the blueberry muffin, which was soft, fresh, and delicious. The ambiance was perfect with a green wall and plants that made it super cute and cozy. The service was amazing as well, friendly and helpful staff. I’ll definitely be coming back!

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Outdoor patio / terrace

reviews_data.review_text: Iced white chocolate latte, really good! Will definitely be back.

I ordered a SF vanilla latte with one shot - they first made it with 2 shots and when I asked them to remake it, they used the same cup just dumped out the original drink. Can confirm they did not use SF vanilla as my blood sugar shot up to 300. Very rude customer service when ordering - these baristas treat customers like a bother rather than a blessing. Definitely not returning after the inconsiderate and rude service ….

The atmosphere was very refreshing, the music they played made the coffee even more enjoyable😎, and the staff were friendly and welcoming. A great little spot to relax and sip! Super clean!

Thank you Hilltop Coffee:)
My favorite intimate coffee and conversation spot! The iced americano with marshmallow and caramel and cream is impeccable and made with love and precision.

I think the customer service needs work, they ladies up front seem antisocial. The new chai is too spicy, the old one was amazing. I tried a regular latte and it was good. I just feel awkward in the shop, it doesn’t feel welcoming enough for me to come back with my work laptop. If the place was bigger than maybe, but smaller shops need more intimacy for me.
Hilltop is a quaint coffee shop that offers serenity and awesome customer service (Valerie and LP) with delicious drinks and pastries. So happy to have a place such as this to retreat to!
Great place with cozy vibes ✨

Love, love, love!! After my first visit, I’ve been here nearly every day. First of all, the staff is LOVELY. My first time there, I asked for a recommendation on a matcha latte, so I gave the Pistachio and Honey syrups a try and it was AMAZING. I genuinely look forward to my visits every day. This was such a wonderful addition to the neighborhood.

Absolutely love this place! Being an entrepreneur and working from home sometimes I need a break from the house.  The iced coffee is amazing! Staff friendly and the interior is cozy with minimalist vibes.  I've been having all my meetings here as well! #BOBsupporter
Nice, cute, little coffee shop. The blueberry muffin was delicious!

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Outdoor patio / terrace

reviews_data.review_text: This place is a new Charlotte Gem!!!! Customer service was amazing. Oh, and a blueberry muffin 20 out of 10. Can’t wait to go back. Also, did I mention it’s black on?

Matcha was top tier
Customer Service exceptional!!!

Chai latte nearly flavorless, however I’ve tried a pistachio honey latte which was certainly on point. The staff is friendly and professional. Word on the street is that a new more authentic spiced Chai may be coming soon. I’m glad that they’ve come to the neighborhood.

The customer service was not good. I was really excited about supporting this business. Especially due to the proximity of my residence (walking distance).  Also, wanted to support a Black-owned business instead of the two (2) Starbucks near my house. Our chai-latte on ice was mainly whole milk and ice. The danish I ordered was burnt in appearance and taste. The Barista seemed like she was annoyed when asked a simple question. These days people like myself work to Io hard for money. There are a plethora of places in Charlotte to get a coffee and a pastry. I made a choice to support this business. I will not be returning or encouraging anyone to support this business. Chic-Fila chicken sandwich is no better than McDonald's chicken sandwich. It really all comes down to great customer service.  That's all!

I had the iced coffee, and it was definitely a good one as a coffee lover. The cafe was clean and nice and seemed like a nice conversational spot. The worker who was working today at 1:00PM was not friendly and  ice cold. I spoke and she didn’t even speak back. It seemed like she had an issue, but it is not for me to try and figure that out. Such a nice cafe deserves a friendlier personality. Her customer service was lacking, it almost gave intolerance and racism. I hope she improves because I will be back. I’m trying to support small, black owned local businesses. The owner should consider customer service and diversity training for the worker. She puts  off very cold, intolerant and negative energy.
I love Hilltop Coffee Shop. Much needed addition to the neighborhood!

This coffee shop was nice, quiet and relaxing. The Violet Blossom Matcha latte was delicious. A nice place to get your work done. Everyone was very friendly in here plus the prices were good, reasonable.

The iced matcha latte is so good! I add oat milk with vanilla, but today I added vanilla and lavender. I love this place!! :)) When it’s busy and no parking spots, you will have to park down the street where there’s a parking lot for the other stores and walk to the cafe.

Black owned coffee shop in Charlotte that is amazing, clean, peaceful, relaxing, and offers a robust cold brew coffee that hits! Valerie is a great barista who is incredibly sweet and welcoming. Support black owned coffee and small businesses!

Went for the first time today and I am overall satisfied with the service, food, and atmosphere of the place. I even stuck around and worked for a couple of hours. I’ll definitely be back again and again.
Great coffee, great service.  What else is there to say?

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Outdoor patio / terrace

reviews_data.review_text: Very cute black-owned coffee shop. The employees are always so sweet. Its great to have a local option nearby. I recommend the lavender matcha, hot or iced. Pastries have been pretty yummy too.
Pistachio Latte is 👌🏼
Amazing owner and quality food and drinks !
This is a nice quaint spot to grab coffee, Cherry Blossom Late, and a cherry scone.
Awesome atmosphere and really kind people working behind the counter. Really looking forward to making this a regular stop for coffee.
Parking is awful, but drinks and the pastries are really good. I’m here at least once a week!
I ordered a matcha latte with lavender—it’s much better than any other shop around. 10/10, highly recommend!

The white chocolate iced latte might be one of my favoritesnin the Charlotte area.

This place is a little small so I would not recommend for group studying but definitely come on a nice day. Very clean spot.

It’s alright. Came today, really excited a coffeeshop moved in that was within walking distance. The decor is very HGTV white with no personality and there are only tables and a bar. There are no four top tables which would be an issue to bring a group. The coffee and matcha lemonade were strong. The baristas were all nice but a little unsure of themselves. I’m sure they will settle in with time. The pastries were way over sweetened, but nothing was dry nor lacking in flavor. A place to return but I’ll ask for less sweetener in my coffee. It isn’t a place I’d come to spend hours because it lacks that comfortability.

As we continued our tour of local coffee shops around the Charlotte area, our last stop brought us to Hilltop Coffee.  The coffee shop was super clean with several places to sit.  The coffee was really good.  The parking lot is tiny, maybe enough space for 7-10 cars at most.  If you are ever headed out shopping on the Mallard road area, stop by for some coffee, it will be worth it.

I have truly found my new favorite coffee shop! I get an almond milk latte with the marshmallow syrup and it's so good, every time! The staff is so friendly (shoutout Sam!) and they are super quick. 10/10!
Not realizing this gem was so close to my job - I would have went in sooner!! Clean, cute and friendly!! I got the americano with almond milk and cranberry scone(yummy). Highly recommend

My friend and I agreed this is the best coffee we’ve had in so long. I moved to CLT a year ago and have been looking for an iced honey lavender latte that tasted this good. The service was great and it was incredibly clean. I was greeted by the owner who was so friendly and I could tell she was excited about this place. 10/10 would recommend.

I was excited to try a new coffee shop in my area but unfortunately didn’t have a good experience.

The customer service was not good - the girl who took my order was rude and the two baristas working were not engaging with customers at all. They completely ignored me when I thanked them for making my drink.

On top of that, my drink was made wrong. I asked for one pump of flavoring but there must have been at least 3 or 4, because it completely overpowered the flavor of what I think would have been a good coffee drink otherwise! I don’t think I’d go back solely based off the customer service, though
Super friendly and cheerful staff. Nice, clean space. Absolutely delicious cold brew and super tasty pastries.
Great service, amazing lattes, and an even better vibe!

I dropped in while I was visiting Charlotte and if I lived here, I would go all the time. This coffee shop is gorgeous and the staff is very kind. The iced mocha was delicious and the croissant was light and fluffy. The service was quick as well. Truly the only downside was the $1 up charge for oat milk which is steeper than most coffee shops charge, but overall this place is affordable for the value you’re getting. This area of Charlotte was in desperate need for another good coffee joint and they are definitely filling that need. Thank y’all!

reviews_data.review_text: This place is very cute and coffee tasted so great.. love the vibe and staff is super friendly and welcoming!!

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Outdoor patio / terrace

reviews_data.review_text: First time visit disappointed, ordered hot latte I got cold, ordered banana nut muffin I got blueberry. I didn’t have time to wait for them to change it. It wasn’t busy, they should have got it right the first time
The coffee is good.  It's small but both times I've been there, I've been able to find a spot to sit. The people working there were nice.
One of the worst chai lattes I’ve ever had.
Gr8

We really wanted to like Hilltop Coffee in Charlotte but it was a downer. The coffees that we got—Hot Pistachio latte and Cold Pistachio Mocha—didn’t taste great at all. The pistachio syrup that was used overpowered the taste of the coffees to the extent that we couldn’t drink them after a few sips.

The location of the shop is a bit precarious too in that you’ve to take an immediate sharp turn to reach here. The few parking spots that are available are quite tight as well.

The staff tries their best and there’s a restroom available inside. Some seating is available both inside and outside.

I recommend finding some other coffee shop if you’re looking for good coffee.

OBSESSED. This place is an absolute gem! The vibes are immaculate, the food is chef’s kiss, and the lattes? Life-changing. Bonus points: the owner is a proud Howard grad—so you know it’s got heart and soul. Do not leave without trying the vanilla oat milk latte (trust me, it’s a whole moment) and the Greek yogurt parfait? Pure bliss in a bowl.
I highly recommend this coffee shop. I received excellent service and the scone was delicious.  I also enjoyed my cappuccino I will definitely come back.
Great community spot —the staff was friendly, coffee and food was delish!I love love the decor and the service was fast. Come on in!
Their Matcha (add expresso and simple syrup, my preference) and jalapeño scones are amazing

I love to have other coffee options other than the large chain shops.
It's kind of hard to see from the main road. It's located/situated in an awkward corner of the road.
I don't care for the parking lot. I can see turning in being a nightmare because of the corner lot being so close to the main road. There are maybe about 8-10 tight parking spots. I can imagine if they are all full people will keep driving

I walked in and was greeted nicely. I ordered the hot Chai with caramel,  it was really good.
It's small and cozy inside. Great spot to come and work remotely or pick up a drink and a quick snack. Outside seating was a plus.
I do recommend trying it.
No one answers the phone to set up group events. Disappointing on that aspect. They just opened so that may be why. I'll add to the review after our event scheduled for April 3rd.
Great service and really good coffee and the owner is so sweet and personable.
Lovely new coffee shop with pleasant baristas

My wife and I went here early on a Saturday morning as we like to try as many coffee places as we can. We order a cappuccino and americano for drinks and a chocolate croissant, almond croissant, and English cranberry scone for pastries. The croissants were dry and chewy (tasted a day old but not sure if they were). We got there at 730 so I would assume they get their pastries delivered first thing in the morning but didnt they didn't taste fresh. The coffee was decent. It is a quaint little spot for a morning coffee.

Cozy Vibes and a Perfect Work Spot

This coffee shop is exactly what the area needs. I stopped in to cowork with a friend and was extremely pleased with the overall vibe. The decor is warm and inviting—just the kind of space that makes you want to settle in. And yes, I have a thing for bathrooms, and they did their big one with the design in there.

While working, I had a traditional latte with almond milk and a toasted chocolate croissant both were delicious and gave me the fuel I needed to focus. The café had a steady stream of customers, from casual walk-ins to folks getting work done. There's outdoor seating and a parking lot, which makes it even more convenient. Definitely adding Hilltop Coffee to my regular rotation.
Excited to finally have a local coffee shop near my house! Cute decor, very chic and modern. Typical coffee options and some pastries as well.

This place is so beautiful! I love how clean and modern it looks on the inside. The staff was very friendly and the coffee was amazing and for a good price! This will be one of my new favorites in Charlotte!
Great cappuccino & very friendly staff

Came in to try it out and we will definitely be return customers. The baristas were so kind and answered all of my questions.

We ordered a chai latte with espresso as well as a customized matcha latte. Both were amazing! The croissants were impeccable.

I love how clean and airy the shop is. 10/10!!!
Good coffee place in a neighborhood with quiet ambience. We tried Lavender latte and it’s a 4/5 which is quite good. Try it!!!

Fiancé had a vanilla iced latte and almond croissant, after a sip and a bite she said she wants to go here every day.
There is outdoor seating so bring a book and relax outside.
I strongly recommend this coffee shop not only for the quality but for the passion they put into making everything fantastic.

First off- this is so close to me. I’m so happy we have a choice other than genocide supporter Starbucks and Dunkin Donuts. Second, the coffee is perfection! I got 3 vanilla lattes so far this week and it is consistent and super delicious. The inside is super clean, the ladies at the front were friendly enough. All in all- I hope Hilltop Coffee stays here a looong time.
Vanilla latte was good and a good price! Will be back soon 😊.

Prices are around your average coffee shops in my opinionn and worth paying for instead going to the usual ⭐️bucks. The base menu is pretty simple and you can alter it based on your preferences (syrups, milk options, etc.) I got an iced vanilla latte with oat milk with a butter croissant. The latte was so good, the proprtion to the coffee vs milk was perfect for my taste buds as i find some places put too much milk esp when you get it iced. Service was very friendly and they were quite busy which was nice to see for a newly opened business. Parking is limited but there are some areas to park in the area and you can walk to the coffee shop (however, park at your own discretion if you do this). I'm really glad a good coffee shop opened up near where I live, finally something other than ⭐️bucks. Will be coming back!
Found this hip spot while on a trip. Great atmosphere, good music, tasty cold brew!

I just had the most amazing almond milk vanilla latte - it truly hugged my soul. Just what I needed to start my day. Staff was so kind and friendly. 1000000% recommend this spot for coffee, atmosphere and the croissants looked amazing, although Im trying to stay away from bread :)

This new coffee shop is an absolute gem! The staff is warm and welcoming, and the decor is flawless, clean, and thoughtfully designed. I ordered a caramel iced latte with oat milk, and it was hands down the best I’ve ever had—perfectly balanced and absolutely delicious. I also picked up a couple of scones, which were just as amazing. I can't wait to come back and make this a regular spot! Highly recommend!
The English Jalapeño scone, pistachio latte and superb service with a boutique vibe! Just what I need to get me to the end of this week.  See you tomorrow!

Their selection is small and prices are high. The customer service could be better, especially for being a brand new. The young ladies at the counter seemed to be annoyed when I asked them questions about their menu. They looked at each other and would laugh/grin, it didn’t feel like a good first experience.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Marissa. Thank you for visiting us. We appreciate your time and value your feedback during our soft opening where we have great opportunities to make adjustments. We sincerely apologize for your less than satisfactory experience and will continue to strive for excellence. Please feel free to email info@hilltopcoffeeclt.com for us to further address your concern and take corrective action that offers the pleasurable experience we strive for. We look forward to hearing from you to resolve this matter.

reviews_data.review_text: Very nice coffee shop, Chai Latte was good.

I went the first week it opened and it was by far the best latte I’ve had in Charlotte! The staff were extremely nice. There was a bit of a wait on drinks because it was so busy—the staff (I think maybe an owner?) checked on all of us and offered free pastries for the wait, so I’d say the service is really good, too. I’ll definitely be back and am SO happy we have a new local coffee shop in the University area!
Great prices on the coffee and the jalapeño scone is amazing
Good coffee and pastries with a nice, pleasant atmosphere. I think the inside could fit 2-3 more tables but overall a welcomed addition of a coffee shop besides Starbucks to the north Charlotte area!
Beautiful and cozy setting, friendly service. Amazing coffee!
Baristas were kind and answered my questions without issues! The coffe was great also I got a vanilla and honey latte
Latte was amazing!

I was impressed from the moment I opened the door. From the warm welcome from passionate staff to the beautiful yet thoughtful decor and layout.   The coffee was so good and the warm jalapeño cheese scone was the perfect mate. I even got to meet the owners, who should be very proud of Hilltop. It's my new favorite coffee shop !

We have been waiting for the spot to open. What a great surprise! A light bright cozy coffee place with superb customer service. Joy and her team will make you feel at home and even welcome your puppy :-) delicious coffee and pastries.
Very cute new coffee shop, loved my matcha drink and the pastries were massive and delicious!

review_questions.null: Dietary restrictions, Parking, Kid-friendliness, Wheelchair accessibility

reviews_data.review_text: Excellent service and drinks.   I got an iced mocha, and my husband got a caramel latte.   We were both extremely satisfied.    The pastries looked fluffy and fresh.   I was eyeing the chocolate croissant but was still full from breakfast!

First time checking out hilltop coffee today and I will definitely be back. The employees are so sweet and the atmosphere is great. Not to mention the coffee and pastries are delicious as well definitely go check them out.

I live right by Hilltop. I could not wait for them to open and be able to walk over for coffee! They did not disappoint. The coffee and pastries are delicious. The atmosphere and staff are great! Thank you for opening up in the area!

What a great little coffee shop! Pastries look delicious and the coffee was so good! The first sip we all said Wow this coffee is really good! The atmosphere is clean and bright   We will definitely be back!
This place is so pretty and the coffee is great! I got a latte with oat milk and it was awesome! The people here are also really nice! Love seeing new places like this already doing so well!

Really quaint atmosphere. I had the moca which was rich and frothy. The service was excellent and the owner was kind and worked upfront with her employees which I really liked and it seemed like a really great work environment. The only drawback I had is the lack of seating but it is kinda a granted because of the small building but full 5 stars would highly recommend!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you, Jason. It was nice meeting you. Hope to see you soon.

reviews_data.review_text: Really comfortable seating and the jalapeño & cheddar scones were soo good!
What a great new space! The lavender latte was out of this world. The baristas are cheery and gracious. I cannot wait to try their other creations.
I just got a latte and MAN o MAN. It’s amazing! So excited for a great coffee shop in the area!

Service, food and atmosphere were excellent! Joy, Rashad and the team were so great and made the experience even better! Oh, and the music... spot on! I encourage everyone to go, I will DEFINITELY be back!

So great to have a local coffee shop in the University City/Mallard Creek area…and oh what a lovely space!  The atmosphere is inviting and comfortable.  We tried a dirty chai latte, a toasted marshmallow latte, and the cheddar jalapeño scone…all were delicious!  The owners, Joy and Rashad, are so friendly, kind, and gracious.  Mariah, the cashier was also awesome!  The other staff, Mariah, and the owners checked on us during our visit.  I can’t wait to go back!  I’m craving a scone!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Your scone is waiting for you!! Come by in the morning. We are so grateful to be able to serve the community.

Black owned coffee shop in Charlotte that is amazing, clean, peaceful, relaxing, and offers a robust cold brew coffee that hits! Valerie is a great barista who is incredibly sweet and welcoming. Support black owned coffee and small businesses!

Went for the first time today and I am overall satisfied with the service, food, and atmosphere of the place. I even stuck around and worked for a couple of hours. I’ll definitely be back again and again.
Great coffee, great service.  What else is there to say?

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Outdoor patio / terrace

reviews_data.review_text: Very cute black-owned coffee shop. The employees are always so sweet. Its great to have a local option nearby. I recommend the lavender matcha, hot or iced. Pastries have been pretty yummy too.
Pistachio Latte is 👌🏼
Amazing owner and quality food and drinks !
This is a nice quaint spot to grab coffee, Cherry Blossom Late, and a cherry scone.
Awesome atmosphere and really kind people working behind the counter. Really looking forward to making this a regular stop for coffee.
Parking is awful, but drinks and the pastries are really good. I’m here at least once a week!
I ordered a matcha latte with lavender—it’s much better than any other shop around. 10/10, highly recommend!

The white chocolate iced latte might be one of my favoritesnin the Charlotte area.

This place is a little small so I would not recommend for group studying but definitely come on a nice day. Very clean spot.

It’s alright. Came today, really excited a coffeeshop moved in that was within walking distance. The decor is very HGTV white with no personality and there are only tables and a bar. There are no four top tables which would be an issue to bring a group. The coffee and matcha lemonade were strong. The baristas were all nice but a little unsure of themselves. I’m sure they will settle in with time. The pastries were way over sweetened, but nothing was dry nor lacking in flavor. A place to return but I’ll ask for less sweetener in my coffee. It isn’t a place I’d come to spend hours because it lacks that comfortability.

As we continued our tour of local coffee shops around the Charlotte area, our last stop brought us to Hilltop Coffee.  The coffee shop was super clean with several places to sit.  The coffee was really good.  The parking lot is tiny, maybe enough space for 7-10 cars at most.  If you are ever headed out shopping on the Mallard road area, stop by for some coffee, it will be worth it.

I have truly found my new favorite coffee shop! I get an almond milk latte with the marshmallow syrup and it's so good, every time! The staff is so friendly (shoutout Sam!) and they are super quick. 10/10!
Not realizing this gem was so close to my job - I would have went in sooner!! Clean, cute and friendly!! I got the americano with almond milk and cranberry scone(yummy). Highly recommend

My friend and I agreed this is the best coffee we’ve had in so long. I moved to CLT a year ago and have been looking for an iced honey lavender latte that tasted this good. The service was great and it was incredibly clean. I was greeted by the owner who was so friendly and I could tell she was excited about this place. 10/10 would recommend.

I was excited to try a new coffee shop in my area but unfortunately didn’t have a good experience.

The customer service was not good - the girl who took my order was rude and the two baristas working were not engaging with customers at all. They completely ignored me when I thanked them for making my drink.

On top of that, my drink was made wrong. I asked for one pump of flavoring but there must have been at least 3 or 4, because it completely overpowered the flavor of what I think would have been a good coffee drink otherwise! I don’t think I’d go back solely based off the customer service, though
Super friendly and cheerful staff. Nice, clean space. Absolutely delicious cold brew and super tasty pastries.
Great service, amazing lattes, and an even better vibe!

I dropped in while I was visiting Charlotte and if I lived here, I would go all the time. This coffee shop is gorgeous and the staff is very kind. The iced mocha was delicious and the croissant was light and fluffy. The service was quick as well. Truly the only downside was the $1 up charge for oat milk which is steeper than most coffee shops charge, but overall this place is affordable for the value you’re getting. This area of Charlotte was in desperate need for another good coffee joint and they are definitely filling that need. Thank y’all!

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Outdoor patio / terrace

reviews_data.review_text: This place is very cute and coffee tasted so great.. love the vibe and staff is super friendly and welcoming!!

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Outdoor patio / terrace

reviews_data.review_text: First time visit disappointed, ordered hot latte I got cold, ordered banana nut muffin I got blueberry. I didn’t have time to wait for them to change it. It wasn’t busy, they should have got it right the first time
The coffee is good.  It's small but both times I've been there, I've been able to find a spot to sit. The people working there were nice.
One of the worst chai lattes I’ve ever had.
Gr8

We really wanted to like Hilltop Coffee in Charlotte but it was a downer. The coffees that we got—Hot Pistachio latte and Cold Pistachio Mocha—didn’t taste great at all. The pistachio syrup that was used overpowered the taste of the coffees to the extent that we couldn’t drink them after a few sips.

The location of the shop is a bit precarious too in that you’ve to take an immediate sharp turn to reach here. The few parking spots that are available are quite tight as well.

The staff tries their best and there’s a restroom available inside. Some seating is available both inside and outside.

I recommend finding some other coffee shop if you’re looking for good coffee.

OBSESSED. This place is an absolute gem! The vibes are immaculate, the food is chef’s kiss, and the lattes? Life-changing. Bonus points: the owner is a proud Howard grad—so you know it’s got heart and soul. Do not leave without trying the vanilla oat milk latte (trust me, it’s a whole moment) and the Greek yogurt parfait? Pure bliss in a bowl.
I highly recommend this coffee shop. I received excellent service and the scone was delicious.  I also enjoyed my cappuccino I will definitely come back.
Great community spot —the staff was friendly, coffee and food was delish!I love love the decor and the service was fast. Come on in!
Their Matcha (add expresso and simple syrup, my preference) and jalapeño scones are amazing

I love to have other coffee options other than the large chain shops.
It's kind of hard to see from the main road. It's located/situated in an awkward corner of the road.
I don't care for the parking lot. I can see turning in being a nightmare because of the corner lot being so close to the main road. There are maybe about 8-10 tight parking spots. I can imagine if they are all full people will keep driving

I walked in and was greeted nicely. I ordered the hot Chai with caramel,  it was really good.
It's small and cozy inside. Great spot to come and work remotely or pick up a drink and a quick snack. Outside seating was a plus.
I do recommend trying it.
No one answers the phone to set up group events. Disappointing on that aspect. They just opened so that may be why. I'll add to the review after our event scheduled for April 3rd.
Great service and really good coffee and the owner is so sweet and personable.
Lovely new coffee shop with pleasant baristas

My wife and I went here early on a Saturday morning as we like to try as many coffee places as we can. We order a cappuccino and americano for drinks and a chocolate croissant, almond croissant, and English cranberry scone for pastries. The croissants were dry and chewy (tasted a day old but not sure if they were). We got there at 730 so I would assume they get their pastries delivered first thing in the morning but didnt they didn't taste fresh. The coffee was decent. It is a quaint little spot for a morning coffee.

Cozy Vibes and a Perfect Work Spot

This coffee shop is exactly what the area needs. I stopped in to cowork with a friend and was extremely pleased with the overall vibe. The decor is warm and inviting—just the kind of space that makes you want to settle in. And yes, I have a thing for bathrooms, and they did their big one with the design in there.

While working, I had a traditional latte with almond milk and a toasted chocolate croissant both were delicious and gave me the fuel I needed to focus. The café had a steady stream of customers, from casual walk-ins to folks getting work done. There's outdoor seating and a parking lot, which makes it even more convenient. Definitely adding Hilltop Coffee to my regular rotation.
Excited to finally have a local coffee shop near my house! Cute decor, very chic and modern. Typical coffee options and some pastries as well.

This place is so beautiful! I love how clean and modern it looks on the inside. The staff was very friendly and the coffee was amazing and for a good price! This will be one of my new favorites in Charlotte!
Great cappuccino & very friendly staff

Came in to try it out and we will definitely be return customers. The baristas were so kind and answered all of my questions.

We ordered a chai latte with espresso as well as a customized matcha latte. Both were amazing! The croissants were impeccable.

I love how clean and airy the shop is. 10/10!!!
Good coffee place in a neighborhood with quiet ambience. We tried Lavender latte and it’s a 4/5 which is quite good. Try it!!!

Fiancé had a vanilla iced latte and almond croissant, after a sip and a bite she said she wants to go here every day.
There is outdoor seating so bring a book and relax outside.
I strongly recommend this coffee shop not only for the quality but for the passion they put into making everything fantastic.

First off- this is so close to me. I’m so happy we have a choice other than genocide supporter Starbucks and Dunkin Donuts. Second, the coffee is perfection! I got 3 vanilla lattes so far this week and it is consistent and super delicious. The inside is super clean, the ladies at the front were friendly enough. All in all- I hope Hilltop Coffee stays here a looong time.
Vanilla latte was good and a good price! Will be back soon 😊.

Prices are around your average coffee shops in my opinionn and worth paying for instead going to the usual ⭐️bucks. The base menu is pretty simple and you can alter it based on your preferences (syrups, milk options, etc.) I got an iced vanilla latte with oat milk with a butter croissant. The latte was so good, the proprtion to the coffee vs milk was perfect for my taste buds as i find some places put too much milk esp when you get it iced. Service was very friendly and they were quite busy which was nice to see for a newly opened business. Parking is limited but there are some areas to park in the area and you can walk to the coffee shop (however, park at your own discretion if you do this). I'm really glad a good coffee shop opened up near where I live, finally something other than ⭐️bucks. Will be coming back!
Found this hip spot while on a trip. Great atmosphere, good music, tasty cold brew!

I just had the most amazing almond milk vanilla latte - it truly hugged my soul. Just what I needed to start my day. Staff was so kind and friendly. 1000000% recommend this spot for coffee, atmosphere and the croissants looked amazing, although Im trying to stay away from bread :)

This new coffee shop is an absolute gem! The staff is warm and welcoming, and the decor is flawless, clean, and thoughtfully designed. I ordered a caramel iced latte with oat milk, and it was hands down the best I’ve ever had—perfectly balanced and absolutely delicious. I also picked up a couple of scones, which were just as amazing. I can't wait to come back and make this a regular spot! Highly recommend!
The English Jalapeño scone, pistachio latte and superb service with a boutique vibe! Just what I need to get me to the end of this week.  See you tomorrow!

Their selection is small and prices are high. The customer service could be better, especially for being a brand new. The young ladies at the counter seemed to be annoyed when I asked them questions about their menu. They looked at each other and would laugh/grin, it didn’t feel like a good first experience.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Marissa. Thank you for visiting us. We appreciate your time and value your feedback during our soft opening where we have great opportunities to make adjustments. We sincerely apologize for your less than satisfactory experience and will continue to strive for excellence. Please feel free to email info@hilltopcoffeeclt.com for us to further address your concern and take corrective action that offers the pleasurable experience we strive for. We look forward to hearing from you to resolve this matter.

reviews_data.review_text: Very nice coffee shop, Chai Latte was good.

I went the first week it opened and it was by far the best latte I’ve had in Charlotte! The staff were extremely nice. There was a bit of a wait on drinks because it was so busy—the staff (I think maybe an owner?) checked on all of us and offered free pastries for the wait, so I’d say the service is really good, too. I’ll definitely be back and am SO happy we have a new local coffee shop in the University area!
Great prices on the coffee and the jalapeño scone is amazing
Good coffee and pastries with a nice, pleasant atmosphere. I think the inside could fit 2-3 more tables but overall a welcomed addition of a coffee shop besides Starbucks to the north Charlotte area!
Beautiful and cozy setting, friendly service. Amazing coffee!
Baristas were kind and answered my questions without issues! The coffe was great also I got a vanilla and honey latte
Latte was amazing!

I was impressed from the moment I opened the door. From the warm welcome from passionate staff to the beautiful yet thoughtful decor and layout.   The coffee was so good and the warm jalapeño cheese scone was the perfect mate. I even got to meet the owners, who should be very proud of Hilltop. It's my new favorite coffee shop !

We have been waiting for the spot to open. What a great surprise! A light bright cozy coffee place with superb customer service. Joy and her team will make you feel at home and even welcome your puppy :-) delicious coffee and pastries.
Very cute new coffee shop, loved my matcha drink and the pastries were massive and delicious!

review_questions.null: Dietary restrictions, Parking, Kid-friendliness, Wheelchair accessibility

reviews_data.review_text: Excellent service and drinks.   I got an iced mocha, and my husband got a caramel latte.   We were both extremely satisfied.    The pastries looked fluffy and fresh.   I was eyeing the chocolate croissant but was still full from breakfast!

First time checking out hilltop coffee today and I will definitely be back. The employees are so sweet and the atmosphere is great. Not to mention the coffee and pastries are delicious as well definitely go check them out.

I live right by Hilltop. I could not wait for them to open and be able to walk over for coffee! They did not disappoint. The coffee and pastries are delicious. The atmosphere and staff are great! Thank you for opening up in the area!

What a great little coffee shop! Pastries look delicious and the coffee was so good! The first sip we all said Wow this coffee is really good! The atmosphere is clean and bright   We will definitely be back!
This place is so pretty and the coffee is great! I got a latte with oat milk and it was awesome! The people here are also really nice! Love seeing new places like this already doing so well!

Really quaint atmosphere. I had the moca which was rich and frothy. The service was excellent and the owner was kind and worked upfront with her employees which I really liked and it seemed like a really great work environment. The only drawback I had is the lack of seating but it is kinda a granted because of the small building but full 5 stars would highly recommend!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you, Jason. It was nice meeting you. Hope to see you soon.

reviews_data.review_text: Really comfortable seating and the jalapeño & cheddar scones were soo good!
What a great new space! The lavender latte was out of this world. The baristas are cheery and gracious. I cannot wait to try their other creations.
I just got a latte and MAN o MAN. It’s amazing! So excited for a great coffee shop in the area!

Service, food and atmosphere were excellent! Joy, Rashad and the team were so great and made the experience even better! Oh, and the music... spot on! I encourage everyone to go, I will DEFINITELY be back!

So great to have a local coffee shop in the University City/Mallard Creek area…and oh what a lovely space!  The atmosphere is inviting and comfortable.  We tried a dirty chai latte, a toasted marshmallow latte, and the cheddar jalapeño scone…all were delicious!  The owners, Joy and Rashad, are so friendly, kind, and gracious.  Mariah, the cashier was also awesome!  The other staff, Mariah, and the owners checked on us during our visit.  I can’t wait to go back!  I’m craving a scone!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Your scone is waiting for you!! Come by in the morning. We are so grateful to be able to serve the community.
